The Democratic representative Brad Sherman, who is encouraging a small group in Congress, presents the problems in another way, but comes to the same conclusion.
"Four hundred professors of economics, including three Nobel Prizes, wrote to tell us: we asked Congress not to rush and carefully examine the path to be taken," he said yesterday.
