According to the schedule of the east coast during the new consultations that lasted until after midnight on Saturday, the leaders of the congress reached an agreement around the financial rescue package of $700 billion in total, after several days of discussion - Reuters reported.
We have made important progress - said Nancy Pelosi, the Democratic President of the North American Congress, saying that it is only missing to formalize the agreement in a document.
The commitment on the package was supported by both presidential candidates, Barack Obama and John McCain.
Henry Paulson, the Minister of Finance, speaking about the outcome of the compromise, said: this program will work and it will be efficient but further measures are needed. According to Pelosi, it is not a question of saving Wall Street, but of turning him back into the car of the economy.
The written version of the package was published before the opening of the Asian markets, i.e. Sunday before 8:00 p.m., according to Washington schedule (i.e. before 2:00 p.m. on Monday, according to Central Europe timetable), without causing a spectacular leap in the bags.
On the bill called emergency law for economic stabilization in 2008, Monday will first vote for the North American Congress and then the Senate.
President George W. Bush on Saturday night consulted with Pelosi and then the White House also celebrated the news of the agreement.
We are pleased with the progress made during the night and highly appreciate the efforts of both parties to stabilize our financial markets and protect our economy - said Tony Fratto, the spokesman for the White House.
The program is different from the Bush administration's original proposal to spend all $700 billion to buy bad-quality credit fund securities.
Now only half of the $700 billion can be spent, using $250 billion immediately after Congress votes, probably on Monday, of this amount, the Ministry of Finance will buy credit fund securities, bad rating securities and the destination of another $100 billion depends on the President's decision.
This programme will be controlled by a special agency, in which the President of the Federal Reserve will also participate.
The other half of the $700 billion can be spent after a new decision by Congress.
Under the law the Ministry of Finance can apply a combined approach: it can simultaneously buy bad credits, mortgages and securities credit fund values, and other "venomous" type credits as well.
The purchase can be made in auctions or in direct form - competent persons of the ministry were informed.
The law allows the affected companies to participate in an insurance program where the finance portfolio guarantees the worrying elements, for which the companies will pay the amount corresponding to the foreseeable damage.
Henry Paulson stated: the law thus ensures the necessary financial means, which can even reach 700 billion dollars to meet the urgent needs of the US financial system, to be the purchase of bad financial means, their insurance or the prevention of risks that could lead to the collapse of some large financial institutions.
We do everything necessary to be ready to introduce the law as soon as they sign it - he added.
On the other hand, the heads of the banks in trouble and waiting for State aid will be able to count on the official limitation of their compensation, which the American argot calls simply parachutes of gold.
Only in certain cases will payments be limited, and the limitations depend on the form of aid from the Ministry of Finance.
The limitation means that if the ministry buys under a auction, an extra tax will be imposed on gold parachutes, unless the failed bank head jubilates.
By buying the bad credits directly, the government will aggressively intervene to ensure that the compensation of the bosses is not exaggerated.
In addition to the above, existing gold parachute contracts will not be changed, the limitations relate only to new contracts to encourage participation in the programme as well.
This is the first case in American history that will be in force a legal limitation for the revenue of directors generals - said Democrat Barney Frank, chairman of the Congress commission, responsible for financial services.
The State will also have the right to acquire shares from the banks participating in the programme, thereby reducing the risk of taxpayers, as they will eventually even be able to obtain profits from the transaction as soon as the economy and the bank recovers.
According to the bill in the next five years, the President will have to make a proposal to Congress on how to return taxpayers to financial sector losses.
Of course, on both sides, there were those who expressed their reservations about the project.
This is not what the American citizens, that is, they are not protecting the taxpayers' dollars, said the California Republican Congressman, Darrell Issa.
